The paper discusses an enhancement to HDFS and Hadoop MapReduce that improves the runtime of MapReduce jobs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes changes to the upload pipeline of HDFS to create different clustered indexes on each data block replica, which suggests that it may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance improvements of HAIL in terms of query execution, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an aggressive approach to improving the performance of yellow elephants, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
